  "id": "BIT-java-min-2024-47546",
  "summary": "GHSL-2024-243: GStreamer has an integer underflow in extract_cc_from_data leading to OOB-read",
  "details": "GStreamer is a library for constructing graphs of media-handling components. An integer underflow has been detected in extract_cc_from_data function within qtdemux.c. In the FOURCC_c708 case, the subtraction atom_length - 8 may result in an underflow if atom_length is less than 8. When that subtraction underflows, *cclen ends up being a large number, and then cclen is passed to g_memdup2 leading to an out-of-bounds (OOB) read. This vulnerability is fixed in 1.24.10.",
  "aliases": [
    "CVE-2024-47546"
